Exercise 13.20: Explain what happens when we copy, assign, or destroy
objects of our TextQuery and QueryResult classes from § 12.3 (p. 484).

Answer:
    Assign + Copy:
        QueryResult:
            - Synthesized assignment or copy will be called which in turn will call the assignment of string, StrBlob, and shared_ptr.
        TextQuery:
            - Synthesized assignment or copy will be called which in turn will call the assignment of StrBlob and map.
and if we destroy them then the Synthesized destructor will be called

Exercise 13.21: Do you think the TextQuery and QueryResult classes
need to define their own versions of the copy-control members? If so, why?
If not, why not? Implement whichever copy-control operations you think
these classes require.

Answer:
TextQuery and QueryResult don't require copy-control members because the synthesized versions can use the copy-control members for each of it
members.